		<time itemprop="dateCreated" datetime="2010-04-14T11:53:35+00:00">April 14, 2010 at 11:53 am</time></a>	</div>

	<div itemprop="text"><p>Could you clarify this &#8220;registration&#8221; mechanism? Currently I&#8217;ve had to hardcode my plugins to look for &#8220;post&#8221; or &#8220;page&#8221; before publishing them. Is there some other way to tell what&#8217;s a really legitimate &#8220;post&#8221; instead of some kind of funky non-post metadata?</p>
<p>I mean, I think it&#8217;s more than a little bit stupid to have to have special code to check whether something that you get from the &#8220;post_publish&#8221; hook is really an actual post. But it could be ameliorated if there&#8217;s a way for plugins to tell whether custom types are real posts or fake posts like nav-menu-item.</p>
</div>

